summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on the United Nations Mission of Observers in Prevlaka (UNMOP), 
Adopted resolution 1437 (2002) on 11 October 2002,

 Reaffirming Croatia's sovereignty and territorial integrity,

Noting the Joint Declaration of 1992 and the Agreement on Normalization of Relations of 1996,

Observing a stable situation in the UNMOP area, 


1. Extends UNMOP's mandate until 15 December 2002;
2. Requests the Secretary-General to prepare for termination of UNMOP's mandate by reducing personnel;
3. Requests a report on completion of UNMOP's mandate;
4. Calls on parties to comply with the demilitarized regime and cooperate with UN observers;
5. Welcomes progress in normalization of relations between Croatia and Yugoslavia;
6. Expresses readiness to review the duration of UNMOP's mandate;
7. Decides to remain seized of the matter
